----ENDF/B-VIII.0     MATERIAL 51                                   51 1451     
-----THERMAL NEUTRON SCATTERING DATA                                51 1451     
------ENDF-6 FORMAT                                                 51 1451     
                                                                    51 1451     
******************************************************************  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* Temperatures = 283.6, 293.6, 300.0,                            *  51 1451     
*         323.6, 350.0, 373.6, 400.0,                            *  51 1451     
*         423.6, 450.0, 473.6, 500.0,                            *  51 1451     
*         523.6, 550.0, 573.6, 600.0 K, 623.6 K                  *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* Extrapolated temperature = 650.0 K                             *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* This evaluation is based on the CAB Model for heavy water[1]   *  51 1451     
* in a liquid state, T < T-crit(D2O) = 643.8 K. The file (MF7)   *  51 1451     
* was generated using NJOY 99.396[1] with a patch (upcab). One   *  51 1451     
* temperature point at 650 K was added for backward              *  51 1451     
* compatibility with ENDF/B-VII.1 scripts.                       *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* The CAB model is a further development of ENDF/B-VII (2006)    *  51 1451     
* and IKE, Stuttgart (2005) models for heavy water (n + D2O);    *  51 1451     
* vibrational spectrum decomposition is applied. For oxygen      *  51 1451     
* (O-16) in D2O, a new evaluation of the scattering kernel was   *  51 1451     
* prepared (free gas model is not applied). The continuous       *  51 1451     
* spectrum is based on MD GROMACS Calculations[2] and diffusion  *  51 1451     
* coefficients measured by Yoshida[3] and Mills[4].              *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* For n + O-16-in-D2O, Skold approximation was applied for       *  51 1451     
* coherent inelastic correction with partial structure factors   *  51 1451     
* validated against experimental data measured by Soper[5].      *  51 1451     
* sig_coh(O-16)/sig_s(O-16) = 1.0 .                              *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* The scattering kernels for H-2-in-D2O and O-16-in-D2O were     *  51 1451     
* tested with criticality calculations in collaboration with     *  51 1451     
* D. Roubtsov from Canadian Nuclear Laboratories[6].             *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* The evaluation was prepared by:                                *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* J.I. Marquez Damian, F. Cantargi, and J.R. Granada             *  51 1451     
* Nuclear Data Group - Neutron Physics Department                *  51 1451     
* Centro Atomico Bariloche - Argentina (CAB):                    *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
*  and                                                           *  51 1451     
*                                                                *  51 1451     
* D. Roubtsov                                                    *  51 1451     
